Class EntrySetPopulatedTests

java.lang.Object
myTest.EntrySetPopulatedTests
public class EntrySetPopulatedTests extends Object
This test case tests the EntrySet class instances linked to a populated map. Every method of the EntrySet class is tested to ensure the class implementation serves correctly as a view for maps with multiple entries. For each method, tests are created to ensure correct behavior in normal and edge cases, including correct handling of contained and non-contained elements, correct throwing of exceptions, and correct return values and side effects on the underlying map.
See Also:
  • MapAdapter
  • MapAdapter.EntrySet
  • MapAdapter.Entry
Design
This test case aims to verify the correct behavior of populated entry set instances to ensure it correctly serves as a set view for maps with entries and implements correctly the HSet interface.
Libraries
JUnit 4.13, Hamcrest 1.3

    • testContainsNotAnEntry

      public void testContainsNotAnEntry()
      Tests the contains method of the EntrySet class with an entry that is not an instance of Entry.
      Design
      Verifies that the contains method throws ClassCastException when called on a non HMap.HEntry object.
      Description
      The contains method is called on the entryset generated in the setUp() phase with a String as parameter. Since a non HMap.HEntry parameter was provided the method is asserted to throw ClassCastException.
      Preconditions
      The EntrySet instance must be initialized and populated with entries.
      Postconditions
      The EntrySet is unchanged
      Expected Results
      The contains method should throw ClassCastException for objects that are not instances of HMap.HEntry.

    • testEntrySetRetainAllWithNullElements

      public void testEntrySetRetainAllWithNullElements()
      Tests that the MapAdapter.entrySet() retainAll method handles a collection containing null elements safely (by treating them as not present).
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.entrySet() retainAll method does not throw exception when called with a collection containing null elements.
      Description
      A NullableHMap instance is created and populated with a null key-value pair. The retainAll method is then called. Since the null entry matches nothing in the map, all elements should be removed.
      Preconditions
      The map is correctly instantiated and populated with 100 items. A NullableHMap is created with null elements.
      Postconditions
      The map is empty.
      Expected Results
      The retainAll method completes without exception and empties the map.

      Tests that the MapAdapter.entrySet() removeAll method handles a collection containing null elements safely.
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.entrySet() removeAll method does not throw exception when called with a collection containing null elements.

      Postconditions
      The map is unchanged
      Expected Results
      The removeAll method completes without exception and the map remains unchanged.

    • testEntrySetContainsAllWithNullElements

      public void testEntrySetContainsAllWithNullElements()
      Tests that containsAll launches NullPointerException when called on a entrySet using entries with null keys or values
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.entrySet() containsAll method returns false when called with a collection containing null elements.
      Description
      Three NullableHMap instances are created and populated with all the permutations of null key or value (null=null,null=value,key=null). The containsAll method is then called on each NullableHMap to assert the correct throwing of NullPointerException.
      Preconditions
      The map is correctly instantiated and populated with 100 items. Three NullableHMap are created and populated with all the permutations of null key or value (null=null,null=value,key=null)
      Postconditions
      The map is unchanged
      Expected Results
      The containsAll method throws NullPointerException
